earn /ɜːn/

(earning,earned,earns) 

1. V-T If you earn money, you receive money in return for work that you do. 挣 (钱) 

例： What a lovely way to earn a living. 一个多好的谋生方式啊！ 

2. V-T If something earns money, it produces money as profit or interest. 赢 (利) 

例： ...a bank account that earns little or no interest. …一个很少或不生利息的银行账户。 

3. V-T If you earn something such as praise, you get it because you deserve it. 赢得 

例： Companies must earn a reputation for honesty. 公司必须赢得诚信。

</div>

